definition.value: A pyridone that is pyridine-2,5-dione which is substituted at positions 3 and 6 by hydroxy groups. A metabolite of the agrochemical, chlorpyrifos.
An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is (9Z)-octadec-9-enoic acid (oleic acid) in which a hydrogen at position 17 has been replaced by a hydroxy group.

A member of the class of phenylethanolamines that is phenylethanolamine in which the the phenyl group is substituted at the para- position by a methoxy group, while the am no group is substituted by a 4-(p-nitrophenyl)butan-2-yl group. A beta-adrenergic agonist that has been used illegally in China as an animal feed additive to as a growth promotion to enhance the the lean meat-to-fat ratio for livestock.
An L-arginine derivative in which the delta-nitrogen atom carries a methyl group; major species at pH 7.3.
An L-arginine derivative in which the omega-nitrogen atom carries a hydroxy group and the delta-nitrogen atom carries a methyl group; major species at pH 7.3.

An alpha,beta-unsaturated aldehyde that is octa-2,7-dienal which is substituted by a hydroxy group at position 8, methyl groups at positions 2 and 6, and in which both double bonds have E configuration.
A beta-D-glucoside resulting from the formal condensation of the omega-hydroxy group of 16-hydroxyhexadecanoic acid (16-hydroxypalmitic acid) with beta-D-glucose.
An alkylglycerol that is glycerol in which the hydrogen of one of the primary hydroxy groups has been replaced by a dodecyl group.
An organic cation resulting from the deprotonation of the phosphate group and protonation of the alpha-amino and imine nitrogens of the L-arginine moiety of L-arginyl-AMP; Major species at pH 7.3.
A diterpenoid compound having a dolabellane skeleton.

An imidohydrazide resulting from the formal condensation of the hydrazide carbonyl group of N'-(p-chlorophenyl)-3,3-dimethyl-2-oxobutanehydrazide with the amino group of p-chloroaniline. A potent and selective antagonist of sphingosine-1-phosphate receptor 3 (S1PR3).

A secondary carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of O-phospho-D-serine with the amino group of m-octylaniline. An analogue of sphingosine-1-phosphate (S1P), it is a potent antagonist for both S1P1 and S1P3 receptors. It can inhibit S1P-induced migration of thyroid cancer cells, ovarian cancer cells, and neural stem cells.

A hydrochloride resulting from the formal reaction of NSC 23766 with 3 mol eq. of hydrogen chloride. An inhibitor of the signalling G-protein known as RAC1 (Ras-related C3 botulinum toxin substrate 1).
